stored_articles.title: Delegation Carries Suffrage Petition
stored_articles.snippet: South Australian suffragists presented a petition with over 11,000 signatures to parliament.
stored_articles.full_text: The Women's Suffrage League delivered a petition exceeding 11,000 signatures to the South Australian Parliament, arguing that women's enfranchisement would strengthen democratic principles and improve social legislation.
stored_articles.summary: South Australian suffragists advanced a mass petition advocating for women's enfranchisement.
summary_bullets: Mary Lee highlighted equity and civic duty.

stored_articles.title: Prime Minister Launches Snowy Scheme
stored_articles.snippet: Prime Minister Ben Chifley officially inaugurated the Snowy Mountains Hydro-Electric Scheme.
stored_articles.full_text: A crowd gathered at Adaminaby to witness Prime Minister Ben Chifley commence construction of the Snowy Mountains Hydro-Electric Scheme. The project promised irrigation for inland farming and renewable electricity for post-war industry.
stored_articles.summary: Ben Chifley opened the Snowy Mountains Scheme, promising power and irrigation for the nation.
summary_bullets: Project positioned as post-war reconstruction effort.

stored_articles.title: Scientists Warn Of Reef Bleaching
stored_articles.snippet: Marine biologists report unprecedented coral bleaching across key sections of the Great Barrier Reef.
stored_articles.full_text: Marine biologists stationed along the Barrier Reef reported extensive bleaching following a month of exceptionally warm waters. Conservation groups urged federal support for monitoring programs and highlighted the need for temperature records.
stored_articles.summary: Survey teams observed bleaching across thirty reef locations after anomalous warm currents.
summary_bullets: Federal funding requested for reef monitoring.
Heat anomalies linked to widespread bleaching.

stored_articles.title: Engineers Outline Multicultural Workforce
stored_articles.snippet: Snowy Mountains Authority reported on its international engineering teams and worker villages.
stored_articles.full_text: The Snowy Mountains Authority detailed the contributions of migrants from more than twenty nations. New worker housing, technical colleges, and safety programs underscored the scheme's scale.
stored_articles.summary: Progress updates highlighted international labour, training, and housing supporting Snowy works.

stored_articles.title: Federation Convention Debates Women's Vote
stored_articles.snippet: Delegates discussed incorporating women's suffrage into the Commonwealth franchise legislation.
stored_articles.full_text: Parliamentary debates in Melbourne grappled with ensuring women across the new Commonwealth would enjoy a uniform franchise. Proponents cited New Zealand's example and the success of South Australia's reforms.
stored_articles.summary: Commonwealth parliament considered universal suffrage, building on earlier colonial reforms.

stored_articles.title: Queensland Communities Rally For Reef
stored_articles.snippet: Local councils coordinated a letter-writing campaign urging reef protections amid tourism expansion.
stored_articles.full_text: Representatives from coastal shires met in Townsville to address reef preservation. They resolved to lobby the Commonwealth for stricter fishing controls and education campaigns aimed at visiting tourists and shipping companies.
stored_articles.summary: Queensland councils organised coordinated advocacy for reef protections amid tourism growth.
summary_bullets: Regional alliance formed to lobby Canberra.
Tourism pressures identified as emerging risk.
